ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Based on your clinical judgement and all that you know of this patient, if untreated, what is the likelihood that this patient will make a suicide attempt in the next 6 months?
Notes: 0 = 0 or no likelihood; 10 = 10 or very high likelihood

ElementDescription: Number of hours spent in  the emergency department for  evaluation, medical/psychiatric treatment, or awaited transfer/discharge.
Patient inclusion criterion was adult status (at least 18 years of age)

Patient exclusion criterion was primarily determined by Clinician to be the presence of any factor that impaired the ability to comprehend and effectively participate in the study, including inability to speak English, gross cognitive impairment, or extremely agitated or violent behavior.
Patient prediction. What is the likelihood that you will make a suicide attempt in the future?
Had a history of multiple suicide attempts
Implicit Association Test (IAT) score of association between death/suicide and self
Implication Association Test (IAT) score of association between life and self
